HEADWORD: Bibliomancy
<hw>Bib"li*o*man`cy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<ets><?/</ets> book + <ets>-mancy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>bibliomancie</ets>.]</ety> <def>A kind of divination, performed by
selecting passages of Scripture at hazard, and drawing from them
indications concerning future events.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bibliomania</ent>⟦br⟧
